Having been a member here for a couple years now, The Skyline Club is by far the best private club experience we've had. Clients love it. The 36th floor views always wow and service is perfectly extraordinary. The food was always very good - but the new chef has really stepped the menu up into what I'd now consider culinary art.

We came to enjoy the Devour menu as we had never been here.  The view was amazing. We did go on a beautiful night!! The food was delicious. The service was also wonderful. Wolfgang, our server, took good care of us! We will definitely be going back!!!

Food was great, but they tack on a service fee and admin fee to your bill. I wish we could of had some warning before hand on the devour Indy website, or maybe on the menu about them charging shipping and handling fees to bring your food out to the table.

A birthday date night led to trying out Skyline Club and as a couple first timers, we weren’t sure what to expect.  36th floor with a spectacular view of Monument Circle and somehow, that became an afterthought.  The food, without question, stole the show.  If you are reading this, the restaurant is usually available to members only.  I’m not sure how long it’ll be open to the public, so take advantage of this while you can.  View – Best in the city Atmosphere – Elegant, up to date Service – Topnotch, start to finish.  Chef came out, GM checked on us and our waitress was fantastic Drinks – Nice selection, started with champaign and then each had a cocktail – I went with a Manhattan and my wife enjoyed a Peach Cosmo FOOD – Skyline Brussels Sprouts, Pan Seared Sea Scallops, Asian Grilled Lamb Chops, Crushed Potatoes.  The brussels sprouts were quite possibly the best I’ve ever had…and when on any menu, I order.  Cooked to perfection with a chili honey glaze spread over goat cheese.  The crushed potatoes were delicious but as the only basic item ordered, got lost in the shuffle.  We brought most of the potatoes home as leftovers and created a breakfast dish the next day that was phenomenal.  As far as the main courses, we haven’t stopped talking about them.  The Pan Seared Sea Scallops dish was incredible and the thoughtfulness of the plating and pairings with corn puree, risotto, bacon and blackberry reduction made it memorable.  The surprise of the night came with the Asian Grilled Lamb Chops.  No words can do this justice and I thank the waitress for introducing this as a popular selection.  Soy glazed with stir fried veggies and a cilantro mint sauce.  3 lamb chop lollipops, which can’t be an easy item to properly cook, were handled by the chef with perfection.  I’ve ordered this dish from a few high-end restaurants and have never left a review or raved to friends about the experience.  We’ve been fortunate to dine at some great restaurants and we both agree, this is now a favorite.  Do yourself a favor and take in the views of the city, enjoy a cocktail and trust the Chef and his team to handle the rest.

A beautiful view of the city and unlike the Eagles Nest won't make you dizzy from the spinning. The server was great, however the food was just average and in my opinion not worth the price. Here you're paying for the view though and in my opinion the food is secondary. Don't go in with super high expectations and just go for the atmosphere and realize the food probably isn't going to wow you.

Great view of the circle from our table, which was decorated for Christmas and very festive. The lobster bisque was very fishy, and would not recommend. Menu felt a little overpriced compared to what we received, but would recommend for the service, atmosphere and view.

The ambience is perfect and the view of monument circle amazing. That alone makes it worth coming here on a special occasion. The cocktail menu seems limited and could include some sweeter cocktails. The food is very good and the brussel sprouts is among the best in Indy. It is made to perfection. The vegetarian entree tastes good too, but the grilled cauliflower is a little underwhelming. The bill includes a service charge even for a couple people. Overall a good spot for a special occasion.
